===Etymology 1===
From {{inh|en|enm|abraiden}}, {{m|enm|abreiden|t=to start up, awake, move, reproach}}, from {{inh|en|ang|ābreġdan|t=to move quickly, vibrate, draw, draw from, remove, unsheath, wrench, pull out, withdraw, take away, draw back, free from, draw up, raise, lift up, start up}}, from {{der|en|gem-pro|*uz-|t=out}} + {{m|gem-pro|*bregdaną|t=to move, swing}}, from {{der|en|ine-pro|*bʰrēḱ-}}, {{m|ine-pro|*bʰrēǵ-|t=to shine}}, equivalent to {{prefix|en|a|braid}}. Related to {{cog|nl|breien|t=to knit}}, {{cog|de|bretten|t=to knit}}.

